documentation.text:
@dev we search for direct solution from_ to target_.addr
 from_ is the source currency , from_ directly filtered by fromToListEx
 target_
      target_.addr                    is the searched dest currency
                                          addr is directly filtered by fromToListEx
      target_.mingranularity          is the minimum granularity we are searching for
                                          is used by the first filter
      target_.qty                     is the qty we are search, it can be overshoot is cheaper to buy more
      target_.delivery                is the filter for target delivery
                                          delivery is directly filtered by fromToListEx
 searcharg_
      searcharg_.maxquote                 is used by the first filter
      searcharg_.maxavgquote
      searcharg_.maxcount
      searcharg_.used                 memorize the used of order
      searcharg_.remainer IGNORED     should be removed from target_.qty before call

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

supportsInterface(bytes4).details: Returns true if this contract implements the interface defined by `interfaceId`. See the corresponding https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-165#how-interfaces-are-identified[EIP section] to learn more about how these ids are created. This function call must use less than 30 000 gas.
